about.description:
PynamoDB is a Pythonic interface to Amazon’s DynamoDB. By using simple,
yet powerful abstractions over the DynamoDB API, PynamoDB allows you
to start developing immediately.
about.summary: A Pythonic interface for Amazon’s DynamoDB that supports Python 2 and 3.

name: pynamodb
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pynamodb" %}
{% set version = "4.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c0937e2ae0ae4abc174115255e93136a7a28b512046911df1a9e6bc8cb52d7a4

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - blinker >=1.3,<2.0
    - botocore >=1.12.54
    - python-dateutil >=2.1,<3.0.0
    - six

test:
  imports:
    - pynamodb

about:
  home: http://jlafon.io/pynamodb.html
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A Pythonic interface for Amazon’s DynamoDB that supports Python 2 and 3.'

  description: |
    PynamoDB is a Pythonic interface to Amazon’s DynamoDB. By using simple,
    yet powerful abstractions over the DynamoDB API, PynamoDB allows you 
    to start developing immediately.
  doc_url: http://pynamodb.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/pynamodb/PynamoDB

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sodre
